criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion criteria were:

          -  Age more than 18 years old;

          -  Baseline estimated GFR, calculated using the chronic kidney disease epidemiology
             collaboration (CKD-EPI) equation, greater than or equal to 60 ml/min/1.73 m2.

        Exclusion criteria were:

          -  Age less than 18 years old;

          -  Comorbidities potentially affecting renal function (i.e. arterial hypertension,
             diabetes, vasculopathy, etc.;

          -  Chronic administration of drugs able to modify renal blood flow and/or GFR
             (angiotensin converting enzyme-inhibitors (ACEI), angiotensin receptor blockers (ARB),
             calcium channel blockers, loop diuretics etc.);

          -  Pregnancy;

          -  Ultrasound evidence of morphological kidney abnormalities and/or renal artery
             stenosis;

          -  Nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) or contrast media in the 2 days before
             the tests.
